RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypodermic needle
<hw>Hyp`o*der"mic need"le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A small slender hollow metallic tube, sharp-pointed at one end and
fitted at the other end with an adapter of larger internal diameter,
designed for introduction of liquids directly into the bloodstream or
other parts of the body of an animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a <er>hypodermic needle{1}</er> together with an
attached syringe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypodermic syringe</ent>⟦br⟧
